wikipedia_page.main: Moira Anne Elizabeth Astin (née Williams; born 18 February 1965) is an Anglican priest: she has been the Archdeacon of Reigate in the Church of England since 30 October 2016.Astin was educated at Clare College, Cambridge and Wycliffe Hall, Oxford; and ordained in 1996. She was a curate at St Nicolas, Newbury from 1995 to 1999; Team Vicar of Thatcham from 1999 to 2005; Vicar, St James, Woodley from 2005 to 2011; and Vicar of Frodingham with New Brumby from 2011 until her appointment as archdeacon.
